article.headline: IUPUI 65, Centenary 49
article.story: SHREVEPORT, La. (AP) -- Brandon Cole scored 23 points to lead IUPUI to a 65-49 win over Centenary Thursday night, giving the Jaguars their first-ever Mid-Continent regular season championship title. George Hill added 15 points for the Jaguars (18-7, 13-1 Mid-Continent), who secured the top seed in the March 4 conference tournament with the win. Alexander Starr led the Gents (4-21, 2-12) with 14 points. IUPUI was a perfect 10-of-10 from the free throw line in the second half, finishing the game 14-of-15. The Jaguars also out-rebounded the Gents 25-19 while holding Centenary to just 18.2 percent (2-of-11) on 3-pointers.
